    • Method Detail

      • getExpression

        public T getExpression()
        Returns:
        a PsiExpression which result is pushed to the stack, or null if this instruction is not bound to any particular PsiExpression

      • getExpressionRange

        public TextRange getExpressionRange()
        Returns:
        if non-null, a part of PsiExpression, returned by getExpression() which this instruction actually evaluates. Usable for polyadic expressions like a == b == c: here instruction may evaluate only a == b part.
